{"ts": "2026-07-13T07:47:53Z", "op": "wiki-query", "query": "User asked: \"types of vector search\"\nAnswer the user's question using only the existing wiki/ knowledge base. Return the final user-facing answer directly, with any relevant citations or note if the wiki lacks coverage.", "total_s": 66.944503, "success": true, "tool_calls": [{"tool": "qmd_search_wiki", "duration_s": 52.16451, "error": null}, {"tool": "read_file", "duration_s": 0.005608, "error": null}, {"tool": "read_file", "duration_s": 0.005384, "error": null}, {"tool": "read_file", "duration_s": 0.003166, "error": null}, {"tool": "ls", "duration_s": 0.002058, "error": null}, {"tool": "read_file", "duration_s": 0.030861, "error": null}, {"tool": "read_file", "duration_s": 0.036173, "error": null}, {"tool": "read_file", "duration_s": 0.023105, "error": null}, {"tool": "read_file", "duration_s": 0.029512, "error": null}, {"tool": "read_file", "duration_s": 0.002791, "error": null}, {"tool": "read_file", "duration_s": 0.002636, "error": null}], "report": "The wiki describes four types of vector search:\n\n- Exact Nearest Neighbor (ENN) search: compares a query vector against the full dataset and returns the exact closest results. It is the most precise approach in the wiki’s taxonomy, but can be less practical at large scale because it requires exhaustive comparison.  \n- Approximate Nearest Neighbor (ANN) search: looks for a close-enough match rather than guaranteeing the exact nearest result. The wiki presents it as a speed-versus-accuracy tradeoff that is especially useful for large datasets.  \n- Semantic search: retrieves results based on meaning and intent rather than exact keyword overlap. It uses embeddings plus similarity comparison to find semantically related content even when the wording differs.  \n- Sparse vector search: works with sparse high-dimensional representations, where many features are zero. The wiki notes TF-IDF as an example context and says this approach emphasizes efficient retrieval over non-zero features.  \n\nMore generally, the wiki defines vector search as representing queries and documents as vectors and comparing them with similarity metrics such as cosine similarity, especially for semantic retrieval in RAG systems. Sources: wiki/pages/4-types-of-vector-search-in-rag-summary.md, wiki/pages/vector-search.md, wiki/pages/exact-nearest-neighbor-search.md, wiki/pages/approximate-nearest-neighbor-search.md, wiki/pages/semantic-search.md, wiki/pages/sparse-vector-search.md"}
